<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="waste-vt">waste <strong><em>vt</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /weɪst/    美 /weɪst/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>浪费；未充分利用：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>waste energy / opportunities
浪费能源/机会</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Experts believe that people can waste less food by shopping only when it is necessary.
专家们认为，只在需要时购买可以减少食物的浪费。</p><footer>2013 北京</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She’s wasted in her present job.
她做现在的工作真是屈才。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>waste sth on sb / sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Have you been wasting time on computer games?
你一直在浪费时间玩电脑游戏吗？</p></div>

<ul>
<li>waste sth (in) doing sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She <strong>wasted no time</strong> (in) rejecting the job offer (= she rejected the offer immediately).
她当即拒绝了这份工作聘用。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Keep in mind that it is a shame to <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (浪费) food.  （2014 陕西）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. waste  </p></div>